verbose_text: Cytochalasin D, an inhibitor of actin polymerization blocked Acanthamoeba mediated host cell death, confirming that actin mediated cytoskeletal rearrangements play an important role in the pathogenesis of Acanthamoeba [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
